<title>BELGIUM: SALOMON RAISES ARBED TO HOLD.</title>
<headline>SALOMON RAISES ARBED TO HOLD.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Summary of research report - </p>
<p>Co name-----------Sector------Price------Broker-------------</p>
<p>Arbed		 Steel	 3,700  *   Salomon Brothers</p>
<p>COMMENT: 1996 loss of 1.2 billion francs was in line with</p>
<p>estimated 1.3 billion. However, strong rise in cash flow in</p>
<p>second half was surprise and with improving fundamentals for the</p>
<p>steel sector there is no great further downside risk for share</p>
<p>after this year's 33 percent drop. Group net profit forecast for</p>
<p>1997 raised to 1.815 from 1.630 billion francs.</p>
<p>Recommendation: HOLD (VS PVS UNDERPERFORM)</p>
<p>Analyst: Terence Sinclair (*) Date of report: 14/05/97</p>
<p> Estimates:   EPS	  pvs est   P/E     Dividend</p>
<p> 1997	   205 LFR    185 LFR   18.1     45 LFR</p>
<p> 1998	   475 LFR    320 LFR    7.7     50 LFR</p>
